SIMPLE: otherwise
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Otherwise
<hw>Oth"er*wise`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Other</ets> + <ets>wise</ets> manner.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>In a different manner; in another way, or in other
ways; differently; contrarily.</def> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thy father was a worthy prince,⟦br⟧
And merited, alas! a better fate;⟦br⟧
But Heaven thought <qex>otherwise</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>In other respects.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It is said, truly, that the best men <qex>otherwise</qex> are not
always the best in regard of society.</q>
<rj><qau>Hooker.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>In different circumstances; under other conditions;
<as>as, I am engaged, <ex>otherwise</ex> I would accept</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ <xex>Otherwise</xex>, like <xex>so</xex> and
<xex>thus</xex>, may be used as a substitute for the opposite of a
previous adjective, noun, etc.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Let no man think me a fool; if <qex>otherwise</qex>, yet as a fool
receive me.</q> <rj><qau>2 Cor. xi. 16.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Her eyebrows . . . rather full than <qex>otherwise</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Fielding.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>otherworldly</ent>⟦br⟧
